Are the Torah and the Gospels identical?
Nope, Gospels came with new revelation
but confirms the Torah. Hence, the message
is not identical but with similarity and one of it
is that God is absolute in oneness.
Qur'an 2:106, 16:101, 10:94 Explanation:
Are the Torah, the Gospels, and the Qur'an identical?
Nope, Qur'an came with new revelations confirming the Torah and the Gospels.
The revelations in the Torah and the Gospels are not totally different since
all scriptures are consistent with the core message and that is the
absolute oneness of God.
Even if we don't have the original message of the Torah and the Gospels,
the Qur'an as the latest revelation is not totally different from the previous
revelations. If Allah abrogates previous revelations He replace it with something
similar or even better. Unfortunately, just like any prophet, Muhammad (S.A.W.) is
accused of being fabricator (Qur'an 16:101) on many occassions when he
attempts to present verses of God.
Is the Qur'an then a substitution of the Torah and the Gospels.
Yes, but not to the point that we discredit or throw away the message in
the Torah and the Gospels, because again these revelations are
consistent with the revelations in the Qur'an. We use the Torah and the
Gospels as reference to confirm the verses if we have doubts (Qur'an 10:94)
Think of it like new edition of any book, every new edition actually
confirms the previous edition that it was once published and
this one is the latest or revised edition of that book.
Yes, the new edition actually substitutes the previous edition too.
This is general fact, not a contradiction.
